dgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1461–":"1461–Afdød","1454–1484":"1454–1484","1481–1526":"1481–1526","1461–Female":"1461–Afdød","1454":"1454","1484":"1484","1461":"1461","1 January 1481":"1. januar 1481","1481":"1481","1526":"1526","Groton, Sudbury, Suffolk, England":"Groton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","Scotland, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Cambridge, , Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1461–":"1461–Overleden","1454–1484":"1454–1484","1481–1526":"1481–1526","1461–Female":"1461–Overleden","1454":"1454","1484":"1484","1461":"1461","1 January 1481":"1 januari 1481","1481":"1481","1526":"1526","Groton, Sudbury, Suffolk, England":"Groton, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Cambridge, , Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1461–":"1461–Deceased","1454–1484":"1454–1484","1481–1526":"1481–1526","1461–Female":"1461–Deceased","1454":"1454","1484":"1484","1461":"1461","1 January 1481":"1 January 1481","1481":"1481","1526":"1526","Groton, Sudbury, Suffolk, England":"Groton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","Scotland, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Cambridge, , Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Duckett","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): from the Middle English personal name <i>Duket</i>. This may sometimes have been an early Middle English pet form of an Old English <i>Ducc(a)</i>, but was more often a pet form of <i>Marmaduke</i>, especially in Yorkshire (see   Duke  ). <i>Marmaduke</i> itself is from Irish <i>Maol Maedóc</i> ‘servant of Maedóc’, <i>Maedóc</i> being the name of prominent Irish saints of the 6th and 7th centuries."],"variants":[{"name":"Dockett","meanings":["English (Devon): variant of   Duckett  . Alternatively, the name may have arisen from Middle English <i>doke heved</i> ‘duck head’ but there is no evidence that this became a hereditary surname."]},{"name":"Doggett","meanings":["English: variant of   Duckett   with voicing of the medial consonant. Alternatively, the name may also be from a Middle English rhyming pet form of <i>Roger</i> (see   Dodge  ) + the diminutive suffix <i>-et</i>. But whether the medial <i>-g-</i> was pronounced as a stop /g/ (as in <i>dog</i>) or an affricate /dʒ/ (as in <i>Roger</i>) is impossible to tell."]},{"name":"Duke","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>duk(ke)</i>, <i>duck</i>, <i>doke</i>, <i>dook</i> ‘duck’ (Old English <i>dūce</i>), either from a perceived resemblance (perhaps a waddling gait) or from association with wild fowling. Compare   Duck  ,   Drake  .","English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Duk</i> or <i>Duke</i>. In northern England this is usually a pet form of <i>Marmaduke</i>. It may alternatively be a survival of one or more Old English personal names, though it is uncertain whether they were still current in the period of surname formation. Old English <i>Ducc(a)</i> is attested in placenames like Duxford (Cambridgeshire) and Duckington (Cheshire), and was perhaps interchangeable with <i>Docc</i>, attested in Doxey (Staffordshire) and Doxford (Northumberland). <i>Duke</i> could also represent Old English <i>Deowuc</i> (as in Deuxhill, Shropshire). A surname from <i>Marmaduke</i> is on record until at least 1881 and derives from the personal name <i>Marmaduke</i>, apparently an Anglo-Norman French pronunciation of Old Irish <i>Maolmaedóc</i> ‘devotee of <i>Maedóc</i>’; see   Duckett  .","Americanized form of Polish <b>Duk</b>: nickname from <i>dukać</i> ‘to stammer or falter’."]}]},{"name":"Katherine","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: Same as Catherine."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Katherine Duckett was born in 1461, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. She married Andrew Doggett in 1481, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom, and was buried in Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1461–":"1461–Surnud","1454–1484":"1454–1484","1481–1526":"1481–1526","1461–Female":"1461–Surnud","1454":"1454","1484":"1484","1461":"1461","1 January 1481":"1. jaanuar 1481","1481":"1481","1526":"1526","Groton, Sudbury, Suffolk, England":"Groton, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Scotland, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cambridge, , Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1461–":"1461–Kuollut","1454–1484":"1454–1484","1481–1526":"1481–1526","1461–Female":"1461–Kuollut","1454":"1454","1484":"1484","1461":"1461","1 January 1481":"1. tammikuuta 1481","1481":"1481","1526":"1526","Groton, Sudbury, Suffolk, England":"Groton, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cambridge, , Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1461–":"1461–Décédée","1454–1484":"1454–1484","1481–1526":"1481–1526","1461–Female":"1461–Décédée","1454":"